[
  {
    "id": "lesson-1",
    "title": "Introduction to Cantonese",
    "pages": [
      {
        "type": "intro",
        "title": "Introduction to Cantonese",
        "goal": "Greeting people and asking for names"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Basic Greetings",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>Cantonese greetings are often informal. Here are some fundamental ways to greet people.</p>\n          <p>To say hello, you can say <strong>你好</strong> (nei5 hou2). For example:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">你好！</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">nei5 hou2!</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Hello!</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>In the morning, it's common to say <strong>早晨</strong> (zou2 san4), which means \"Good morning\". For example:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">早晨。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">zou2 san4.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Good morning.</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>When parting ways, you say <strong>再見</strong> (zoi3 gin3). For example:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">再見。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">zoi3 gin3.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Goodbye.</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "你好！",
        "romanization": "nei5 hou2!",
        "translation": "Hello!",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/1.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "早晨。",
        "romanization": "zou2 san4.",
        "translation": "Good morning.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/5.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "再見。",
        "romanization": "zoi3 gin3.",
        "translation": "Goodbye.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/6.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Asking for Names & Identity",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>Basic sentence structure in Cantonese is Subject-Verb-Object. <strong>我</strong> (ngo5) is \"I\", and <strong>你</strong> (nei5) is \"you\".</p>\n          <p>The verb for \"to be\" is <strong>係</strong> (hai6), and \"to be called\" is <strong>叫</strong> (giu3).</p>\n          <p>To state your name, you use 叫:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">我叫小明。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ngo5 giu3 siu2 ming4.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">My name is Siu Ming.</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>To ask \"What is your name?\", you ask what name they are called using <strong>咩</strong> (me1 - What) and <strong>名</strong> (meng2 - Name):\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">你叫咩名？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">nei5 giu3 me1 meng2?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">What is your name?</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>To ask \"Who are you?\", you use <strong>邊個</strong> (bin1 go3) for \"Who\":\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">你係邊個？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">nei5 hai6 bin1 go3?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Who are you?</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>You can also state your identity using 係, like <strong>學生</strong> (hok6 saang1 - Student):\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">我係學生。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ngo5 hai6 hok6 saang1.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">I am a student.</span></em><br>\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">你好，我係David。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">nei5 hou2, ngo5 hai6 David.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Hello, I am David.</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>The particle <strong>呢</strong> (ne1) is used as a tag question, similar to asking \"How about...?\":\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">你呢？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">nei5 ne1?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">How about you?</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "你叫咩名？",
        "romanization": "nei5 giu3 me1 meng2?",
        "translation": "What is your name?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/2.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "我叫小明。",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "我",
            "r": "ngo5"
          },
          {
            "t": "叫",
            "r": "giu3"
          },
          {
            "t": "小明",
            "r": "siu2 ming4"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "ngo5 giu3 siu2 ming4.",
        "translation": "My name is Siu Ming.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/3.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "你呢？",
        "romanization": "nei5 ne1?",
        "translation": "How about you?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/4.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "你係邊個？",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "你",
            "r": "nei5"
          },
          {
            "t": "係",
            "r": "hai6"
          },
          {
            "t": "邊個",
            "r": "bin1 go3"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "nei5 hai6 bin1 go3?",
        "translation": "Who are you?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/7.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "我係學生。",
        "romanization": "ngo5 hai6 hok6 saang1.",
        "translation": "I am a student.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/8.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "你好，我係David。",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "你好",
            "r": "nei5 hou2"
          },
          {
            "t": "我",
            "r": "ngo5"
          },
          {
            "t": "係",
            "r": "hai6"
          },
          {
            "t": "David",
            "r": "David"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "nei5 hou2, ngo5 hai6 David.",
        "translation": "Hello, I am David.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/9.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Apologizing",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>When getting someone's attention or apologizing lightly, there is a very common phrase to use: <strong>唔好意思</strong> (m4 hou2 ji3 si1 - Excuse me / Sorry).</p>\n          <p>For example, if you bump into someone or need to politely interrupt, you can say:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">唔好意思。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">m4 hou2 ji3 si1.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Excuse me / Sorry.</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "唔好意思。",
        "romanization": "m4 hou2 ji3 si1.",
        "translation": "Excuse me / Sorry.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson1/10.m4a"
      }
    ],
    "level": "A1"
  },
  {
    "id": "lesson-2",
    "title": "Daily Needs",
    "pages": [
      {
        "type": "intro",
        "title": "Daily Needs",
        "goal": "Shopping and ordering food"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Ordering Food & Drinks",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>When ordering food or shopping, you often use <strong>我要</strong> (ngo5 jiu3) for \"I want\", and <strong>我唔要</strong> (ngo5 m4 jiu3) for \"I don't want\".</p>\n          <p>Cantonese uses classifiers before nouns, especially after numbers. The general classifier is <strong>個</strong> (go3), and for drinks, you use <strong>一杯</strong> (jat1 bui1) for \"one cup of\".</p>\n          <p>For example, to order a pineapple bun (<strong>菠蘿包</strong> - bo1 lo4 baau1), you say:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">我要一個菠蘿包。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ngo5 jiu3 jat1 go3 bo1 lo4 baau1.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">I want a pineapple bun.</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>To order milk tea (<strong>奶茶</strong> - naai5 caa4):\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">我要一杯奶茶。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ngo5 jiu3 jat1 bui1 naai5 caa4.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">I want a cup of milk tea.</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>To ask if they have water (<strong>水</strong> - seoi2), you use <strong>有冇</strong> (jau5 mou5) for \"Do you have?\":\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">有冇水？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">jau5 mou5 seoi2?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Do you have water?</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>If you don't want something, simply say:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">我唔要。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ngo5 m4 jiu3.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">I don't want (it).</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "我要一個菠蘿包。",
        "romanization": "ngo5 jiu3 jat1 go3 bo1 lo4 baau1.",
        "translation": "I want a pineapple bun.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/1.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "我要一杯奶茶。",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "我",
            "r": "ngo5"
          },
          {
            "t": "要",
            "r": "jiu3"
          },
          {
            "t": "一杯",
            "r": "jat1 bui1"
          },
          {
            "t": "奶茶",
            "r": "naai5 caa4"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "ngo5 jiu3 jat1 bui1 naai5 caa4.",
        "translation": "I want a cup of milk tea.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/4.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "有冇水？",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "有冇",
            "r": "jau5 mou5"
          },
          {
            "t": "水",
            "r": "seoi2"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "jau5 mou5 seoi2?",
        "translation": "Do you have water?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/7.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "我唔要。",
        "romanization": "ngo5 m4 jiu3.",
        "translation": "I don't want (it).",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/8.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Shopping & Prices",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>When buying items, you'll need to ask for the price. To point at something, use <strong>呢個</strong> (ni1 go3) for \"This one\", and ask <strong>幾多錢</strong> (gei2 do1 cin2) for \"How much money?\".</p>\n          <p>For example:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">呢個幾多錢？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ni1 go3 gei2 do1 cin2?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">How much is this?</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>You can express your reaction to the price. <strong>好貴呀</strong> (hou2 gwai3 aa3) means \"Very expensive\", and <strong>好平</strong> (hou2 peng4) means \"Very cheap\".</p>\n          <p>Examples:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">好貴呀。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">hou2 gwai3 aa3.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">It's so expensive.</span></em><br>\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">好平。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">hou2 peng4.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">It's very cheap.</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "呢個幾多錢？",
        "romanization": "ni1 go3 gei2 do1 cin2?",
        "translation": "How much is this?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/2.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "好貴呀。",
        "romanization": "hou2 gwai3 aa3.",
        "translation": "It's so expensive.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/5.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "好平。",
        "romanization": "hou2 peng4.",
        "translation": "It's very cheap.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/6.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Politeness in Service",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>In a cha chaan teng (Hong Kong style café), <strong>唔該</strong> (m4 goi1) is the magic word for ordering, asking for the bill, or requesting things. It means \"Thank you (for service) / Please\".</p>\n          <p>For a gift or a compliment, you use <strong>多謝晒</strong> (do1 ze6 saai3) to say \"Thank you very much\".</p>\n          <p>When you are ready to pay, you ask for the bill with <strong>埋單</strong> (maai4 daan1).</p>\n          <p>Examples:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">唔該。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">m4 goi1.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Please / Thank you.</span></em><br>\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">多謝晒。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">do1 ze6 saai3.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Thank you very much.</span></em><br>\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">唔該，埋單。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">m4 goi1, maai4 daan1.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">The bill, please.</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "唔該。",
        "romanization": "m4 goi1.",
        "translation": "Please / Thank you.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/3.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "多謝晒。",
        "romanization": "do1 ze6 saai3.",
        "translation": "Thank you very much.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/9.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "唔該，埋單。",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "唔該",
            "r": "m4 goi1"
          },
          {
            "t": "埋單",
            "r": "maai4 daan1"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "m4 goi1, maai4 daan1.",
        "translation": "The bill, please.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson2/10.m4a"
      }
    ],
    "level": "A1"
  },
  {
    "id": "lesson-3",
    "title": "Time & Routines",
    "pages": [
      {
        "type": "intro",
        "title": "Time & Routines",
        "goal": "Discussing time and daily schedule"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Telling Time",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>Time markers typically come before the verb in Cantonese. To say \"now\", you use <strong>依家</strong> (ji1 gaa1). To ask \"What time?\", you use <strong>幾點</strong> (gei2 dim2).</p>\n          <p>For example:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">依家幾點？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ji1 gaa1 gei2 dim2?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">What time is it now?</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>To talk about waking up, use <strong>起身</strong> (hei2 san1). \"Seven o'clock\" is <strong>七點</strong> (cat1 dim2).</p>\n          <p>For example, to ask someone when they wake up:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">你幾點起身？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">nei5 gei2 dim2 hei2 san1?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">What time do you get up?</span></em><br>\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">我七點起身。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ngo5 cat1 dim2 hei2 san1.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">I get up at seven.</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "依家幾點？",
        "romanization": "ji1 gaa1 gei2 dim2?",
        "translation": "What time is it now?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/1.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "你幾點起身？",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "你",
            "r": "nei5"
          },
          {
            "t": "幾點",
            "r": "gei2 dim2"
          },
          {
            "t": "起身",
            "r": "hei2 san1"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "nei5 gei2 dim2 hei2 san1?",
        "translation": "What time do you get up?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/4.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "我七點起身。",
        "romanization": "ngo5 cat1 dim2 hei2 san1.",
        "translation": "I get up at seven.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/5.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Parts of the Day",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>Cantonese divides the day clearly with time-related vocabulary. <strong>晏晝</strong> (aan3 zau3) is afternoon, and <strong>晚</strong> (maan5) is evening. \"Tonight\" is <strong>今晚</strong> (gam1 maan5), and \"Tomorrow night\" is <strong>聽晚</strong> (teng1 maan5).</p>\n          <p>Asking \"Have you eaten yet?\" using <strong>食飯</strong> (sik6 faan6) is a common social greeting.</p>\n          <p>If you want to say you have time (<strong>時間</strong> - si4 gaan3), you can say:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">今晚有時間。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">gam1 maan5 jau5 si4 gaan3.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">I have time tonight.</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>More Examples:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">我晏晝食飯。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">ngo5 aan3 zau3 sik6 faan6.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">I eat in the afternoon.</span></em><br>\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">聽晚見。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">teng1 maan5 gin3.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">See you tomorrow night. (見 gin3 = See/Meet)</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "我晏晝食飯。",
        "romanization": "ngo5 aan3 zau3 sik6 faan6.",
        "translation": "I eat in the afternoon.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/2.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "聽晚見。",
        "romanization": "teng1 maan5 gin3.",
        "translation": "See you tomorrow night.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/3.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "今晚有時間。",
        "romanization": "gam1 maan5 jau5 si4 gaan3.",
        "translation": "I have time tonight.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/9.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "learn",
        "title": "Frequencies & Days",
        "contentHtml": "\n          <p>Expressing how often things happen is useful. <strong>成日</strong> (seng4 jat6) means \"All day\" or \"Always\", while <strong>有時</strong> (jau5 si4) means \"Sometimes\".</p>\n          <p>To talk about the weather, <strong>落雨</strong> (lok6 jyu5) is \"Rain\", and <strong>熱</strong> (jit6) is \"Hot\".</p>\n          <p>Examples:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">成日都落雨。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">seng4 jat6 dou1 lok6 jyu5.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">It rains all day.</span></em><br>\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">有時好熱。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">jau5 si4 hou2 jit6.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Sometimes it's very hot.</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>To ask about tomorrow (<strong>聽日</strong> - teng1 jat6), you can ask what day of the week (<strong>星期幾</strong> - sing1 kei4 gei2) it is:\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">聽日係星期幾？</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">teng1 jat6 hai6 sing1 kei4 gei2?</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">What day is tomorrow?</span></em>\n          </p>\n          <p>A common phrase to say \"Almost there\" or \"That's about it\" is <strong>差唔多啦</strong> (caa1 m4 do1 laa1):\n            <em><span class=\"ex-cn\">差唔多啦。</span> <span class=\"ex-ro\">caa1 m4 do1 laa1.</span> <span class=\"ex-en\">Almost there / That's about it.</span></em>\n          </p>\n        "
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "成日都落雨。",
        "romanization": "seng4 jat6 dou1 lok6 jyu5.",
        "translation": "It rains all day.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/6.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "reading",
        "text": "有時好熱。",
        "romanization": "jau5 si4 hou2 jit6.",
        "translation": "Sometimes it's very hot.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/7.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "聽日係星期幾？",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "聽日",
            "r": "teng1 jat6"
          },
          {
            "t": "係",
            "r": "hai6"
          },
          {
            "t": "星期幾",
            "r": "sing1 kei4 gei2"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "teng1 jat6 hai6 sing1 kei4 gei2?",
        "translation": "What day is tomorrow?",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/8.m4a"
      },
      {
        "type": "practice",
        "exerciseType": "scrambled",
        "text": "差唔多啦。",
        "tokens": [
          {
            "t": "差唔多",
            "r": "caa1 m4 do1"
          },
          {
            "t": "啦",
            "r": "laa1"
          }
        ],
        "romanization": "caa1 m4 do1 laa1.",
        "translation": "Almost there / That's about it.",
        "audio": "audio/lesson3/10.m4a"
      }
    ],
    "level": "A1"
  }
]